headline: Cboe Gets Nod to List Firms in Australia in Threat to ASX
summary: The country’s financial regulator signed off on a listing market application from Cboe’s Australian unit after a review, according to an Australian Securities & Investments Commission statement on Tuesday.  ASIC’s decision will allow initial public offerings on Cboe Australia, threatening to end ASX’s local market domination.
